connection_id hashing: The implementation uses hashlib.sha3_256.
Hyperliquid's docs reference keccak256. Are these the same?
(They are NOT — sha3_256 is NIST SHA-3, keccak256 is Ethereum's
pre-standardised version. If you are unsure which Hyperliquid uses,
flag this as VERIFY.)
EIP-712 domain chainId: The implementation uses chainId: 1337.
Is this correct for Hyperliquid mainnet? (Flag as VERIFY if unsure.)
sign_typed_data call: Does eth_account.Account.sign_typed_data
accept domain_data, message_types, message_data as keyword
arguments in the version installed? Or does it use a different
